The material topics where Siemens can exert the greatest influence on society and the environment are climate action, social and ecological standards in the supply chain, and sustainable product design and lifecycle management. These topics received the highest scores in this year’s analysis.

→ Outsidein perspective: The outside-in perspective refers to sustainability topics that

can be associated with opportunities and risks for the company’s business activities or financial situation. This perspective was taken into account in the inside-out per- spective in order to introduce the double materiality principle of future regulation.